The healthy response rate is only 25%. Hence the Y variable has a high class imbalance. Hence accuracy will not be a reliable model performance measure.

FN is very critical for this business case because a false negative is a person who will potentially may diagonose to have parkinson but who has been classified as 'healthy'. Hence the most relevant model performance measure is recall

Split the person_df into training and test set in the ratio of 70:30 (Training:Test).

In [39]:
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
test_size = 0.30 # taking 70:30 training and test set
seed = 7  # Random numbmer seeding for reapeatability of the code
y = person_df["status"].values
In [40]:
#all dummies

def get_model_data(df):
    
    X = person_df.drop("status" , axis=1)
    X = pd.get_dummies(X, drop_first=True)
    
    X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X, y, test_size=test_size, random_state=seed)

    
    return X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test

def get_recall_score(learning_rate, min_samples_leaf, n_estimators):

    model = GradientBoostingClassifier(**{'learning_rate': learning_rate, 
                  'min_samples_leaf': min_samples_leaf,
                  'n_estimators': n_estimators})
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    return [learning_rate,min_samples_leaf,n_estimators,recall_score(y_train, model.predict(X_train)),
    recall_score(y_test, model.predict(X_test))]

def get_recall_score(min_samples_leaf, n_estimators):

    model = RandomForestClassifier(**{ 
                  'min_samples_leaf': min_samples_leaf,
                  'n_estimators': n_estimators,
    'n_jobs':-1})
    model.fit(X_train, y_train)
    return [min_samples_leaf,n_estimators,recall_score(y_train, model.predict(X_train)),
    recall_score(y_test, model.predict(X_test))]

                  'min_samples_leaf': min_samples_leaf,
                  'n_estimators': n_estimators,

    recall_score(y_test, model.predict(X_test))]

Confusion matrix means

True Positive (observed=1,predicted=1):

Person has symptoms to parkinsons and model predicted that the person has

False Positive (observed=0,predicted=1):

Person did not have symtoms to parkinsons and model predicted that the person has

True Negative (observed=0,predicted=0):

Person did not have symptoms to parkinsons and model predicted that the persons is healthy

False Negative (observed=1,predicted=0):

Person has symptoms to parkinsons and model predicted that the person is healthy

Here the screeners wants person to shedule appointments when they have symptoms. So if we have a person who has symptoms but predicted to be healthy should not be delayed to appointment. Therefore focus shpould be on False negative. Decreasing FN and increasing recall.
